In the bin packing problem, given a set of items of various sizes, the goal is to pack them into the fewest number of bins possible without exceeding the capacity of each bin. In this case, the bins are represented by their current loads, and the item is a float that must be added to one of the bins.

### Heuristics:
Implementing different heuristics can help in finding a good packing without necessarily finding the optimal solution, which can be computationally expensive.

